OL,3,CEx-councillor found guilty of stalking
OL,4,CDame Penny Mordaunt
OL,6,FAn ex-councillor has been found guilty
OL,7,Fof stalking Dame Penny Mordaunt but
OL,8,Facquitted of the more serious offence
OL,9,Fof stalking involving serious alarm or
OL,10,Fdistress.
OL,12,FA jury convicted Edward Brandt of the
OL,13,Flesser charge following a trial at
OL,14,FSouthampton Crown Court, which heard
OL,15,Fthat the former Conservative Party
OL,16,Fleadership candidate feared "sexual
OL,17,Fviolence" and believed the 61-year-old
OL,18,Fwas a "real threat".
OL,20,FThe jury returned the guilty verdict
OL,21,Fby a majority of 10 to two.
